        "text_cMCzKU": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>The term “septic” describes the oxygen-free (anaerobic) environment within the tank, where beneficial bacteria break down and digest household waste.</p><p>However, the use of common household chemicals—such as bleach, antibacterial cleaners, and harsh detergents—can disrupt or kill these vital bacteria. When bacterial levels drop, the system’s efficiency suffers, increasing the risk of clogs, backups, and costly repairs.</p><p>Environmental Biotech offers safe, biologically enhanced treatments that restore and maintain a healthy bacterial balance in your septic system—ensuring long-term performance and reliability.</p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        }
